definition.value: A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from hexadecanoic acid.
A phosphosphingolipid consisting of sphinganine having a phosphocholine group attached to its primary hydroxyl group.
A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from stearic acid.
Any aromatic amide obtained by acylation of aniline.
A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from icosanoic acid.
An organic salt obtained by combining guanidine with one molar equivalent of acetic acid.
A tetracyclic diterpenoid with formula C20H22O5, originally isolated from the dried root outer bark of Tripterygium hypoglaucum.

An abietane diterpenoid that is abieta-8(14),9(11),12-triene substituted at positions 3, 11 and 14 respectively by oxo, hydroxy and methoxy groups. It is found in Tripterygium wilfordii and Tripterygium hypoglaucum.

A member of the class of indazoles that is 1H-indazole that is substituted at position 3 by a 6-(cis-2,6-dimethylmorpholin-4-yl)pyrimidin-4-yl group and at position 5 by a (1-methylcyclopropoxy)group. It is an inhibitor of leucine-rich repeat kinase 2 (LRRK2).
An N-(long-chain-fatty-acyl)-L-glutamic acid in which the acyl group is specified as (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl.
A deuterated compound that is lysne in which the methylene hydrogens at positions 4, 4, 5 and 5 have been replaced by deuterium.
A scalarane sesterterpenoid with formula C26H40O3, originally isolated from the marine sponge Hyrtios erecta.
A diglyceride in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 36 carbons and 6 double bonds.
A diglyceride in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 38 carbons and 9 double bonds.
A diglyceride in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 41 carbons and 1 double bond.
A diglyceride in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 41 carbons and 5 double bonds.
An alpha-D-glucoside that is (27R)-1,27-dihydroxyoctacosan-3-one on which the hydroxyl hydrogen at position 1 has been replaced by an alpha-D-glucosyl residue.
An alpha-D-glucoside that is (27R)-1,27-dihydroxyoctacosan-3-one on which the hydroxyl hydrogen at position 1 has been replaced by an alpha-D-mannosyl residue.
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 16 carbons and 2 double bonds.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is (9Z,11Z,13E,15E)-octadecatetraenoic acid carrying an oxo substituent at position 4.

An isoxazoline that is 4,5-dihydro-1,2-oxazole-3-carboxylic acid in which both of the hydrogens at position 5 have been replaced by phenyl groups. It is used (particularly as its ethyl ester, known as isoxadifen-ethyl, as a herbicide safener, especially in conjunction with the herbicides fenoxaprop-P-ethyl and iodosulfuron-methyl-sodium.

An isoxazoline that is the ethyl ester of isoxadifen. It is used as a herbicide safener, especially in conjunction with the herbicides fenoxaprop-P-ethyl and iodosulfuron-methyl-sodium. It is not approved for use within the European Union.
A deuterated compound that is is an isotopologue of alanine in which all seven hydrogen atoms have been replaced by deuterium.
Any trienoic fatty acid containing 16 carbons.
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 16 carbons and 4 double bonds.
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 17 carbons and 2 double bonds.
Any trienoic fatty acid containing 18 carbons.
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 18 carbons and 4 double bonds.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2,2-dimethyl-3-[(1Z)-3,3,3-trifluoroprop-1-en-1-yl]cyclopropanecarboxylic acid with the hydroxy group of 2,3,5,6-tetrafluoro-4-(methoxymethyl)benzyl alcohol. It is an unspecified mixture of  isomers at the cyclopropane ring; the trifluoropropenyl side-chain has Z configuration. It is an insecticide with rapid knock-down activity.
A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from tetracosanoic acid.
A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from arachidonic acid.
A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from N-[12(S)-hydroperoxy-(5Z,8Z,10E,14Z)]-icosatetraenoic acid.
A fatty acid-taurine conjugate derived from N-[15(S)-hydroperoxy-(5Z,8Z,11Z,13E)]-icosatetraenoic acid.

A monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-{[5-chloro-4-(methylamino)pyrimidin-2-yl]amino}-3-methoxybenzoic acid with the amino group of morpholine. It is an inhibitor of leucine-rich repeat kinase 2 (LRRK2).
An alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
An alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
A dihydroagarofuran sesquiterpenoid and pyridine alkaloid with formula C36H45NO18 originally isolated from Tripterygium wilfordii.
A cyclic spermidine alkaloid that is 2-phenyl-1,5,9-triazacyclotridecan-4-one in which the amino hydrogen at position 9 has been replaced by a furan-3-carbonyl group.
An alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.

An alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.

An alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of beta-galactosidase (EC 3.2.1.23).

An alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.

An alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.

An alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.

An alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.

An alpha-D-Glc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc(PP-Dol)(2-) in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-(1'-sn-glycerol).

An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate group of any oligosaccharide-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine-(1->4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acylglycero-3-phosphoglycerol(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-(Z-alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol); major species at pH 7.3.
